# Markdown Documentation Standards

## Context
- When creating or updating README files
- When writing documentation
- When creating guides or instructions

## Requirements
- Use proper heading hierarchy (# for title, ## for sections)
- Include a descriptive title at the top of each document
- Wrap code snippets in proper markdown code blocks with language specified
- Use bullet points for lists rather than long paragraphs
- Include a Table of Contents for documents longer than 3 sections
- Link to related documents and resources when relevant
- Keep line length under 100 characters
- Use relative links for internal documentation references
- Include setup/installation instructions in project READMEs

## Examples
